  "diary": "Woke up early to that perfect Friday feeling—coffee tasted better than usual. Work was solid; paired with Marcus on some tricky state management stuff, then grabbed lunch at Pike Place. The market was packed, but I found a quiet corner with a decent sandwich and just watched people for a bit.\n\nLeft early to catch the Pride street fair on Capitol Hill. The energy was infectious—rainbows everywhere, live music, food vendors. Grabbed some Thai food and wandered around, ran into a few folks from college. Felt good being part of something bigger than the usual work-home routine. The whole drive back to Magnolia felt mellow; windows down, warm breeze. Spent the evening tinkering with my side project—nothing groundbreaking, but it's nice to build something just for me.",
  "thought_process": "I decided to duck out early and hit the Pride fair because the weather was too perfect to waste, and honestly, I needed a mental break from sprint planning. Work was fine but draining—debugging always puts me in a tunnel. The market walk helped reset me. When I saw the street closures on my calendar this morning, I knew I had to make time for it. There's something about being around that kind of community energy that reminds me why I live here. I skipped going back to the office after lunch because I realized I'd rather be present for something real than squeeze in another meeting. The side project at night was my way of reclaiming creative space after a day of corporate problem-solving.",
